# Code owners for nit.
#
# Each line maps a path (a crate, module, or top-level folder) to one or
# more owners. Owners are automatically requested for review on pull
# requests that touch matching paths, and — with the "main-protection"
# ruleset's "require code-owner review" rule — at least one listed owner
# must approve before the PR can merge.
#
# Rules are evaluated top-to-bottom and the LAST matching pattern wins, so
# the broad default sits first and the per-crate rules below override it
# for their paths. To add a co-owner, append more @handles to a line:
#
#     /crates/nit-tui/    @asheux @collaborator @another
#
# Every handle must be a GitHub user (or team) with at least read access
# to the repo, otherwise GitHub flags the entry as a CODEOWNERS error.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner for anything not matched by a more specific rule below.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
*                       @asheux

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Crates (Rust workspace members)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
/crates/nit/            @asheux
/crates/nit-core/       @asheux
/crates/nit-tui/        @asheux
/crates/nit-games/      @asheux
/crates/nit-gol/        @asheux
/crates/nit-metal/      @asheux
/crates/nit-mcp/        @asheux
/crates/nit-syntax/     @asheux
/crates/nit-utils/      @asheux

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Repo infrastructure, tooling & docs
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/               @asheux
/docs/                  @asheux
/scripts/               @asheux
/vendor/                @asheux
